Seeking talent for Richmond Tourism project - Richmond VA - NU 12/2 or 12/3

URGENT NEW PROJECT JUST IN!  Here is what we know/need:

Client:  Richmond Regional Tourism

Nonunion project

Location:  Richmond VA

Date:  Either 12/2 or 12/3 (be sure to hold availability if you submit)

Rates:

Speaking - $1,000 (less any fees)

Nonspeaking - $500 (less any fees)

Usage:  3 years paid online

Talent needed:

1. Speaking:  30+ male or female. Any ethnicity. Itâ€™s all about the delivery. SELF TAPE REQUIRED FOR CONSIDERATION!

1. Nonspeaking - 30 + couple (non speaking), any ethnicity - will pick from headshots and current photos, but do want actors.  Real couples should apply or willing to put together couple from individual submissions.

Submission process:

Speaking role:  Self tape auditions using this script linked below.  NOTES:  The key is the actor is going to have to memorize it or at least sections of it, so someone who can handle dialogue.  Please be off-book for your audition.  Slate with first and last name then go into the script.  Send your 1 video file to [casting@liquidtalentgroup.com](mailto:casting@liquidtalentgroup.com) by 5 pm on Monday 11/24.  Make sure file is labeled with your name.

SCRIPT:  https://drive.google.com/file/d/1iTDR4CP5BsQIU6yCZ7SKhWIAMc89womz/view?usp=sharing

Nonspeaking roles:  Send current headshot or photo to [casting@liquidtalentgroup.com](mailto:casting@liquidtalentgroup.com) by 5 pm on Monday 11/24.  Make sure file is labeled with your name.  If submitting as a couple, be sure both individuals are in 1 picture and include names of everyone in your email.

Questions?  Let us know!

items.text:
**URGENT!** **We're looking for two on-camera presenters (Male + Female)! Self-tape required by today - please email crewing@freshcutvideo.co.uk for more details on script.**

***Casting Brief:***

**Project:** AI & Accounting Series
**Format:** Green-screen studio, direct-to-camera delivery
**Location:** London
**Shoot:** 25th November
**Usage:** Online, paid media, client channels
**Rates:** Please provide day rate + buyout (include preparation time for learning scripts)

**Overview**

We are casting **one male** and **one female** presenter capable of confidently portraying professional accountants. The content is aimed at small-business owners and accounting professionals, so performances must feel authentic, warm and knowledgeable.

The series includes:
* **Three longform videos (<90 seconds each)**
* **Three social cutdowns (30 seconds each)**

Scripts to be provided in advance.

**Performance Requirements**
* Strong **direct-to-camera** presence; clear, articulate delivery.
* Ability to speak about **AI, finance, and accounting concepts** with confidence (no technical background required, but must be able to convey authority).
* Natural, human, emotive tone â€“ avoid corporate monotone.
* Must be comfortable working with a **teleprompter**, but weâ€™re ideally looking for actors who can **learn scripts in sections** for a more natural flow.
* Able to take direction quickly for pace, tone and clarity.

**Scripts cover topics such as:**
* AI vs automation
* The future of AI in accounting
* Human-in-the-loop systems
* AI efficiency and audit readiness

**Look & Feel**
* Clean, simple green-screen setup.
* Straight-to-camera.
* Professional, friendly, trustworthy.
* No heavy characterisation â€“ this is credible business presentation.

**Casting Specs**

**Female Actor**
* Age: 30â€“50
* Style: Professional, approachable, confident
* Smart-casual wardrobe (own clothes)

**Male Actor**
* Age: 30â€“50
* Style: Professional, approachable, confident
* Smart-casual wardrobe (own clothes)

**Submissions:**

Please send the following to **crewing@freshcutvideo.co.uk**
* CV / Showreel
* Portfolio
* Availability + rates incl. buyout

items.text:
Hi Everyone! I run a nonprofit that provides children who have lost a parent or sibling with a special gift or experience to help them on their grief journey. In June 2026 we are hosting a 5-day free theater day-camp in Boulder for these bereaved children. We are partnering with an Atlanta-based theater company, Destination Theatre. If you or someone you know has a child who would qualify, please feel free to share this information with them. More info is on our website and application. Statistically 1 in 12 children will lose a parent or sibling by the time they are an adult so it is quite possible someone knows someone who would benefit from this experience.  I will be posting this in several groups, so you may see this again!

Take care!

Final-Year University Film (Dissertation Project)

Writer/Director: **Katie Devereux**

Producers: Gemma Brown & [Neil Watt](https://www.facebook.com/groups/579540888783195/user/100009669757495/?__cft__[0]=AZXR6viEXnSn32YGywwwLvkVxMA19kzA78LtpNCHrLooLG4svNhGZHQHcNXuR4_ltXdbeSHbmregFpUDFnMPw6BC9XtGlVFrn857Y103Df9LZHbA6lZo4GNxxe7NB_TgSB7RVALK_GOOSq1UpNcW762Y&__tn__=-]K-R)

DOP: [Ayomide Adesanya](https://www.facebook.com/groups/579540888783195/user/100003027738905/?__cft__[0]=AZXR6viEXnSn32YGywwwLvkVxMA19kzA78LtpNCHrLooLG4svNhGZHQHcNXuR4_ltXdbeSHbmregFpUDFnMPw6BC9XtGlVFrn857Y103Df9LZHbA6lZo4GNxxe7NB_TgSB7RVALK_GOOSq1UpNcW762Y&__tn__=-]K-R)

Filming: **4â€“9 February 2026**

Genre: **Drama / Fantasy / Dark Comedy**

Sub-Genre: **Poetic absurdism / surreal drama**

Logline:

Between life and whatever waits beyond, a woman must confront the gap between the goodness she shows and the truth of her intentions before her fate is decided.

ROLES WEâ€™RE CASTING:

**SERAPHINE (playing age 50â€“70)**

Calm, composed, quietly powerful. She carries a serene, grounded presence with a sharp inner compass. Seraphine is the still point of the Bureau â€” wise, perceptive, procedural, and softly authoritative.

**GREGOR (playing age 30â€“50)**

Weathered yet warm; a street musician who becomes an unexpected mirror for our protagonist. Gentle, perceptive, grounded, and quietly charming. Ideally able to strum a guitar.

**ABOUT THE PROJECT**

This is an unpaid final-year university film, but we treat our productions professionally and take pride in the work. The story blends surreal imagery with emotional truth, focusing on intention, kindness, and self-reflection.

**We offer:**

â€¢â  â Full IMDb credit

â€¢â  â A polished reel cut of your scenes

â€¢â  â UK + international festival submissions

â€¢â  â A creative team with a previous track record of festival success

If these roles resonate with you, or youâ€™re drawn to thoughtful, character-driven stories with a surreal edge, weâ€™d love to hear from you.

Please send headshots, credentials, and a short note on why youâ€™re interested to:

 **scoczechproductions@gmail.com**

A serene presence with sharp inner compass. GREGOR Playing age 30 30-50 50 Weathered, warm, perceptive. A busker with understated wisdom and mysterious undertones. PLEASE APPLY BY 05/12/2025 & EMAIL TO: scoczechproductions@ gmail. ail.com'

**ISO: 15-FT Production Truck Driver (PA)  - Indie Film**

We are seeking a reliable Driver(PA) for our micro-budget indie film.

**Non-Union**

**Location:** Los Angeles Area
**Position:** 15ft Production Truck Driver
**Rate:** $18.19/hour

**Responsibilities:**
* Pick up production truck and deliver to set location
* Return to set after wrap to pick up truck and transport to next location
* Ensure safe and timely transport of production vehicle
* Loading & unloading truck with other assistance

**Work Dates:**
* Thursday, December 4, 2025 (pick up day)
* Friday, December 5, 2025
* Saturday, December 6, 2025
* Sunday, December 7, 2025
* Monday, December 8, 2025
* Tuesday, December 9, 2025
* Friday, December 12, 2025 (potentially - not definite)
* Saturday, December 13, 2025
* Sunday, December 14, 2025
* Monday, December 15, 2025
* Tuesday, December 16, 2025
* Wednesday, December 17, 2025
* Thursday, December 18, 2025 (return day)

**Hours:** These will not be full shooting days. Hours may range from 4 to 6 hours per day as needed for vehicle transport.

**Requirements:**
* Valid driver's license
* Clean driving record
* Experience driving larger vehicles/trucks preferred
* Punctual and dependable

If interested, please submit your resume, a message regarding your interest/experience, and 3 references to info@saltpicturesco.com with your availability and any questions about the position.

items.text:
I've posted on this before and many of you liked it/ agreed with needing all information in a casting call including location, dates, pay etc.

My question is why are people posting what may be legitimate casting calls without the pay information? Like how is this helpful to them or anyone?

I can't think of any job acting or not where you'd have to spend time emailing to show interest; gathering your spotlight (or CV), headshots, showreels etc just to ask for pay. 

I find it frustrating, many clearly don't seem to mind as these posts get a lot of interest but personally seems dodgy to me.

Just needed to ask and get that off my chest.

topComments.text: Full transparency is what is required. I find it pretty bad when these posts say NO PAY. If it's a job, we are entitled to remuneration for the time we put in. We're a business not a charity. How are we expected to pay our bills etc...

Fully agree with you. I don't even mind if it's unpaid, but SAY that. Don't wait until 20 people ask whether it's paid or not to tell us that it isn't, y'know? It feels pretty disrespectful of our time.

I am still looking to cast for the mum and Jay.

Production is taking place in Stoke-On-Trent tomorrow (19th November) please call me on 07507977991 or email me at Jake.jakej@outlook.com 

Thank you, 

Jake

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'Tough, wiry, and street-smart but emotionally scarred. Trying to straight yet haunted by anger and guilt. Deeply protective of Lucy. Needs quiet intensity and physical realism. ay' Vulnerable yet strong. Smart, sensitive, and hopeful despite fear. anchor and the heart of the story. Manipulative, controlling stepfather. Charismatic on the sur- face, violent underneath. coward masked as bully. Worn down and trapped in denial. Loves her children but lacks the strength to protect them. Gruff ex-biker mentor. Represents temptation and belonging from Jay' old life. Eccentric, twitchy biker with dark humour. Adds edge and danger to Jay' world. Email jake.jakej@outlook.com'

May be an image of text that says 'CASTING CALL BREATHING STILLL Jay, a 19-year-old just out of prison, who returns home to protect his younger sister Lucy from their abusive stepfather Tom. As Jay struggles to stay out of trouble, old loyalties and buried rage threaten to drag him back into violence. When Tom' cruelty turns physical, Jay is forced to choose between freedom and doing what's right. *VOLUNTARY ONLY* TRAVEL AND EXPENSES WILL BE PAID FOR'

Immersive Theatre Residency

Learn how to work in the space between you and the other.

11 and 12 December
10.00 to 17.00
Theatre Deli 

Join a two day residency exploring the creation of raw and atmospheric immersive performance. Inspired by the research behind Rotten Meat The Old Kip on Meatham Estate, this residency invites participants to work closely with space, character, and narrative to build intense and emotionally charged encounters.
Through task based improvisation and sensory exploration, you will investigate how bodies respond to environments shaped by tension, uncertainty, and resilience. The work will focus on presence, proximity to the audience, and the construction of meaningful and transformative experiences.
Drawing from Vinicius Sallesâ€™s fifteen years with Punchdrunk and his own extensive research in immersive theatre, the residency offers a practical insight into how narrative, space, and the audience can function together as active partners in performance.
This residency is suitable for performers, dancers, actors, and artists who are curious about immersive theatre and interested in expanding their creative approach.
Expect a challenging and engaging process that invites vulnerability, reflection, and bold artistic experimentation.
This is for artists who want to shape the unknown.

Secure one of the 10 space available, Claim your space in here: https://buytickets.at/murmurcreations/1954127

**CASTING CALL â€” Vancouver, BC**
Looking for actors (18+) to play *16â€“18* for a 4th-year Capilano University short film titled **BOYISH**.

A coming-of-age story about the messy shift from boyhood to adulthood, dumb dares, and the people we meet along the way.

**ROLES:**
**LUKA (lead)** â€” male-presenting, playing 16â€“18. Quiet, awkward, observant.
**YAZ (lead)** â€” male-presenting, playing 16â€“18. Bright, restless, warm.

**Union + Non-Union welcome (volunteer)**
**Filming:** Feb 7â€“9, 2026 (Vancouver)
**Actors must be 18+**

To submit, send headshot + reel to **boyish2026@gmail.com** by **Dec 1st, 2025 â€“ 11:59pm**.
Subject line: **BOYISH â€“ LUKA** or **BOYISH â€“ YAZ**

*Michael Chekhov Europe* invites you to its first workshop in the new year: 

**THE MOVING SPACE: Atmosphere and Playfulness on Stage **

with **David Zinder**, Tel Aviv, **Vladimir Baicher**, Moscow, **Suzana NikoliÄ‡**, Zagreb, **Ulrich Meyer-Horsch**, Hamburg

**January 29 to February 1, 2026 **in Hamburg, Germany 

The space on stage is full of life, full of energy and breath. All an actor has to do is connect to this living space. 

What happens when we dive into the world of a given play and allow ourselves to be surprised by its specific dynamics, energy, language and space? 

Michael Chekhovâ€™s concepts of â€œAtmosphereâ€ (â€œthe soul of every performanceâ€) and â€œThe Feeling of Ease, Form, Beauty and the Wholeâ€ will guide us through this exploration. 

*Movement in Space â€“ Objective Atmosphere â€“ Spatial Relationship â€“ Personal Atmosphere â€“ Feeling of Ease, Form, Beauty and the Whole â€“ Organic breathing â€“ Playfulness â€“ Ensemble *

Michael Chekhov Europe Training â€“ module 2

Tuition fee: 450â‚¬ / 490â‚¬

More information: [[https://sfsh.de/michael-chekhov-module-2/sfsh10037/](https://sfsh.de/michael-chekhov-module-2/sfsh10037/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MghjYWxsc2l0ZQEyAAEeY52GI3lQe3pjPHhDXowpGuLqIQrzJcqGyZcZh3SR3jGKGPx3ohVQgDBpaaY_aem_LqlofjR6f5SXrNzWnHvQPg&brid=aB9vxtDqrKES53cnQp0y_A)](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fsfsh.de%2Fmichael-chekhov-module-2%2Fsfsh10037%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MghjYWxsc2l0ZQEyAAEex7NVSBwXFESZYv0PnNVOZZnSrzpDqZTYYyPIFJFP5nZT3Q26Ztt6WS-2fEA_aem_avdglXTU1DOTHvEm2ODLWw%26brid%3DkHUv4f1OfBXrKWr9lBtxHA&h=AT3aprJLj6mz3iCe_wMtmzrhtZGIayz1KSnpU58Ex7Z3EzPlrdAAC1KuqKpynOGfS5EK5Ig9QN83EuaeroAfCpArCXGbw_dimFyj16sIOeaPH6rPkuzKw_HUwj0Asyp3ugyfD65FobRJTmjdHtFUjy3Q2Q&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT0HA0NarzIKKHpcfuGCk_r7lozXPeUvPcNPcopwlZ-UI1byChoQ3du3h8W5ximHzMBhAEXGkb_bl8TQatSz2VHJa7jDl-KVLtmeALpkJ1DA_bE9mEexuYkjuWUew5yTen0VdKvkkNsZpaSC4X3beQM387ABsSrCYXTYojujQlQB)

***FREE SOLO SHOW CLASS THIS SATURDAY ***

Hello Theatre Community!

Are you curious about creating a ONE PERSON SHOW?

Then you do not want to miss this 100% FREE, 100% AWESOME solo theatre class "The Art of Creating the One Person Show" commencing THIS SAT NOV 22ND @10AM (PST)/12pm (CST)/1pm (EST) via Zoom.

RSVP HERE: [[https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play.../](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR5JOXkrGupSob_aL7XRY7Ik_98-uI11G6oVvxBIC0u-1wdb93899gE0kpTsMQ_aem_NYPp-jb3GhTzidIXnux5pA)](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soaringsolostudios.com%2Ffree-one-person-play-class%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR547mRa3QDqLMFyYTJcGULWCwYNj3MxApUIVLCrl1VpBdhdUfbBoWDYcYLZ8A_aem_DlUN5OUEjtov1q36Cbrbcg&h=AT25Uu8u1Bh833c7rTLN1AuU_1B9ULYYG3Zeyz09wBgWTOWGJWiwn7EWSt5Tvvety3mBpg3QjiTic8DbnjYqPRyUta74dQu_PYjC_NDXS8bc3nQjiD8JQOewzzVexAokXFn_abXGrEmWAjEXL7vgFao&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT2pa-OxMQCeSFwubtmUEZs9QURpCCAc3ME-UwV-zkbSpP63P1ZwKZzy-aq1rgggyCMQy7AcUi5boJGVY0pXy4D1iQ5N3fLH2Js9MU4wvaoJSi3hJYDmz60Atn-gYW1vqgmz696MDvQogRwdwNzVrUNOVSFteuRe_Zh8fe16zw)

I have been teaching this ongoing FREE class for over a decade and I have been working in the genre of Solo Theatre for over 20 years. I have directed & developed well over 175 solo shows and toured successfully with my own award-winning solo shows, and I would be honored and excited to help guide YOU into your own success as a Solo Artist.

**ALL EXPERIENCE LEVELS WELCOME**, and no material needed to bring to the virtual class as I always provide a writing prompt. If you do have a solo excerpt you wish to share, that option will be available too.

All you need to attend this Zoom class is a willingness to explore, something to write with and on, and an RSVP here: [[https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play.../](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR6MpS3AJnmqUOCIMAKTzI2vfZkFDp1yZGGDeU1JCLSmdZKB_zb_NdSfF8_3mQ_aem_CWtiIZXQ6PVSuzhTP1VR_A)](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soaringsolostudios.com%2Ffree-one-person-play-class%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR52cSZXKPPIAuvqVIWO2Etv1tt2108KcEf7erKwl8WgDwuO7gnj8fOnJKTmRg_aem_ZG_LDTB5G5vHvPxm-FKWEA&h=AT25Uu8u1Bh833c7rTLN1AuU_1B9ULYYG3Zeyz09wBgWTOWGJWiwn7EWSt5Tvvety3mBpg3QjiTic8DbnjYqPRyUta74dQu_PYjC_NDXS8bc3nQjiD8JQOewzzVexAokXFn_abXGrEmWAjEXL7vgFao&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT2pa-OxMQCeSFwubtmUEZs9QURpCCAc3ME-UwV-zkbSpP63P1ZwKZzy-aq1rgggyCMQy7AcUi5boJGVY0pXy4D1iQ5N3fLH2Js9MU4wvaoJSi3hJYDmz60Atn-gYW1vqgmz696MDvQogRwdwNzVrUNOVSFteuRe_Zh8fe16zw)

I truly hope you will join the Soaring Solo Community and I for this fabulous virtual event. Let's turn your solo show dreams into an amazing reality!

Jessica

RSVP HERE: [[https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play.../](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR5JOXkrGupSob_aL7XRY7Ik_98-uI11G6oVvxBIC0u-1wdb93899gE0kpTsMQ_aem_NYPp-jb3GhTzidIXnux5pA)](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soaringsolostudios.com%2Ffree-one-person-play-class%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR547mRa3QDqLMFyYTJcGULWCwYNj3MxApUIVLCrl1VpBdhdUfbBoWDYcYLZ8A_aem_DlUN5OUEjtov1q36Cbrbcg&h=AT25Uu8u1Bh833c7rTLN1AuU_1B9ULYYG3Zeyz09wBgWTOWGJWiwn7EWSt5Tvvety3mBpg3QjiTic8DbnjYqPRyUta74dQu_PYjC_NDXS8bc3nQjiD8JQOewzzVexAokXFn_abXGrEmWAjEXL7vgFao&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT2pa-OxMQCeSFwubtmUEZs9QURpCCAc3ME-UwV-zkbSpP63P1ZwKZzy-aq1rgggyCMQy7AcUi5boJGVY0pXy4D1iQ5N3fLH2Js9MU4wvaoJSi3hJYDmz60Atn-gYW1vqgmz696MDvQogRwdwNzVrUNOVSFteuRe_Zh8fe16zw)

I have been teaching this ongoing FREE class for over a decade and I have been working in the genre of Solo Theatre for over 20 years. I have directed & developed well over 175 solo shows and toured successfully with my own award-winning solo shows, and I would be honored and excited to help guide YOU into your own success as a Solo Artist.

**ALL EXPERIENCE LEVELS WELCOME**, and no material needed to bring to the virtual class as I always provide a writing prompt. If you do have a solo excerpt you wish to share, that option will be available too.

All you need to attend this Zoom class is a willingness to explore, something to write with and on, and an RSVP here: [[https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play.../](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR6MpS3AJnmqUOCIMAKTzI2vfZkFDp1yZGGDeU1JCLSmdZKB_zb_NdSfF8_3mQ_aem_CWtiIZXQ6PVSuzhTP1VR_A)](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soaringsolostudios.com%2Ffree-one-person-play-class%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExVzdXRmdWRUUxMUlLWnBSRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR52cSZXKPPIAuvqVIWO2Etv1tt2108KcEf7erKwl8WgDwuO7gnj8fOnJKTmRg_aem_ZG_LDTB5G5vHvPxm-FKWEA&h=AT25Uu8u1Bh833c7rTLN1AuU_1B9ULYYG3Zeyz09wBgWTOWGJWiwn7EWSt5Tvvety3mBpg3QjiTic8DbnjYqPRyUta74dQu_PYjC_NDXS8bc3nQjiD8JQOewzzVexAokXFn_abXGrEmWAjEXL7vgFao&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT2pa-OxMQCeSFwubtmUEZs9QURpCCAc3ME-UwV-zkbSpP63P1ZwKZzy-aq1rgggyCMQy7AcUi5boJGVY0pXy4D1iQ5N3fLH2Js9MU4wvaoJSi3hJYDmz60Atn-gYW1vqgmz696MDvQogRwdwNzVrUNOVSFteuRe_Zh8fe16zw)

Jessica

items.text:
Hi!

I am an acting teacher living between NYC and Paris and I am so excited to be launching my new acting program in Paris! I have been an acting teacher at the Yale School of Drama for over 13 years & I have brought together some of the most outstanding teachers for our first summer - and there are more to come!

Please spread the word?! 

So many opportunities to train in play, clown, voice and movement, and physical acting this Winter and Spring in NYC & Paris! || 

www.theplaysociety.org

items.text:
Casting Call!

We have one role left to cast!!

*Starchild* is a sci-fi drama that follows the story of two scientists, Vanessa and Tanner as they take separate paths to deal with their grief. Vanessa through faith, and Tanner through science. It's not until they discover the origins of life itself, that they reconcile to start a family of their own.

Looking to cast supporting character John Marlow.

The film is heartfelt, honest, and powerful.

Please send resume, headshot, and (if applicable) demo reel to starchildcasting@gmail.com

May be an image of text

May be an image of text that says 'John Marlowe Male Late 30s to 60s Any ethnicity Pastor John carries quiet authority and compassion, arriving with coffee, donuts, and genuine care. He sees through Tanner's defenses in single conversation and challenges him to grieve with honesty his faith grounded in realism. Though a one- scene role, his presence anchors the story's moral compass, bridging belief and understanding. Must bring warmth, presence, and strong listening skills.'

the wait is over! we are now accepting submissions for our summer production of â€œBe More Chill!â€

for full details, visit the link in our bio.

Simone Nathalia - Director/Choreographer
Taylor McKee - Music Director
Madison Raybould - Choreographer
Morgan Da Silva-Rolph - Stage Manager

audition dates
in-person: December 20th & 21st, 2025
callbacks: January 3rd, 2026
self-tapes: submissions due on Dec. 19th

audition venue:
Carousel Theatre for Young People, 1411 Cartwright St, Granville Island

audition requirements:
all roles in this production are volunteer, non-union. xoxo welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and skill levels to audition.

what to prepare:
1. 2 contrasting musical theatre songs, (you may only be asked to sing one, but please have both ready).

2. a 1-2 minute contemporary, comedic monologue - this must be memorized.

how to apply:
please email your headshot and resume to theatre@xoxotv.ca to be scheduled with an audition time, or to request a self-tape submission.

character breakdowns can be found in our â€œaudition packageâ€ link in bio.

production dates:
July 15th - 18th, 2026

production venue:
Firehall Arts Centre, 280 E Cordova St, Vancouver

notes:
rehearsals will begin April 30th, 2026
Saturdays 10:00am to 6:00pm
Tuesdays & Thursdays 6:00pm to 10:00pm

contact info@xoxotv.ca or DM us with any questions!

best of luck to all performers - weâ€™ll see you at auditions! ðŸ˜ðŸ’„ðŸ¾

The world premiere production of Be More Chill was commissioned and originally produced by Two River Theater Company in Red Bank, NJ

**Jigsaw Casting is seeking a Weather Reporter for a Quick Serve Restaurant Campaign across Canada**

We are also open to a host or news reporter. Theyâ€™re likeable, relatable, charming, and capable of giving an authentic performance. The ideal candidate has real-life reporting experience. The age range is 40s. Someone that knows the weather like the back of their hand, the subtlety and nuances. Theyâ€™re confident and engaging, with a comedic sensibility.

This will be filming in Toronto. If someone lives far from this area, travel and accommodation will be provided.

**IF YOU KNOW OF SOMEONE, PLEASE PASS THIS ON!**

This is a non union job. Compensation if selected: $3,075.00. Buyout is based on survival of the edit and includes all lifts, edits, versions.

Recall: Wed Nov 26th, 2025 in Toronto Studio or via zoom if you live far away from Toronto.

Wardrobe: Dec 5th, 2025.

Shoot Date: Dec 9th with a weather hold of Dec 10th, 2025.

*Talent will be shooting outside, in Toronto.

items.text:
FOR VALID EUROPEAN PASSPORT HOLDERS ONLY !!

We are a professional dance company and we are looking for professional dancers to work with us (dance show) during summer season 2026 ( from mid March-Octobrt) at 5 and 4 star hotels in Crete , Greece .

We provide accommodation , insurance and contract.

If you want to have the opportunity to be part of our professional team and live  under the Cretan sun , then this your chance. 

Send us your CV at pastoumarilena@yahoo.com , so we can arrange your interview and give you more information. 

Messages sent at messenger wonâ€™t be answered. Only e-mails , please.

Best Regards,

Marilena.

My name is Jerry Valentino Wright â€” published author of 11 books and creator of multiple cinematic universes that are READY to be adapted to film.

Iâ€™m seeking one serious, visionary producer or small production company who sees potential where others see limits â€” someone who wants to help bring a powerful, original franchise to life.

I have several finished books that are visually explosive, emotionally gripping, and built for the screen, including:

ðŸŽ¬ The Eternal War: Light vs Darkness â€”
A supernatural action-drama with apocalyptic tension, angelic warfare, moral conflict, and a lead character whose destiny shifts the balance between Heaven and Hell.

ðŸŽ¬ Edge of the Block (series) â€”
Urban, gritty, raw, perfect for a streaming series or limited-run Netflix-style drama.

ðŸŽ¬ No Mercy Left, The Last Revelation, The Final Prophecy â€”
End-times thrillers with cinematic visuals, spiritual depth, and blockbuster potential.

These arenâ€™t â€œideas.â€
These are published works, already moving thousands of readers â€” stories built with character arcs, emotional weight, and world-building filmmakers dream about.

Iâ€™m looking for the RIGHT partner:
ðŸ‘‰ A producer with vision
ðŸ‘‰ A director who loves building new worlds
ðŸ‘‰ An indie studio hungry for original IP
ðŸ‘‰ Someone who wants to turn books into films with real impact

If youâ€™re interested in reading the logline, synopsis, or treatment â€” or if youâ€™re a filmmaker who loves collaborating with authors â€” comment below or DM me directly.

Letâ€™s build something legendary.
Letâ€™s create a film people will feel, not just watch.

â€” Jerry Valentino Wright
Author | Creator | Visionary Storyteller

âœ¨ Only 20 participants - selective casting.

We - a partner of TikTok, Entertainment Agency - are filming a professional educational course on TikTok Live Sales.
We are currently selecting students who will:
ðŸŽ“ appear on camera as the classroom audience
ðŸ“˜ and simultaneously receive real training in TikTok Live Sales techniques.

What you will gain:
â€¢ Practical skills for working in TikTok Live
â€¢ A clear understanding of how a selling livestream is structured
â€¢ The possibility of being included in the exclusive creator pool of our agency, working in a professional studio equipped for TikTok livestreams
â€¢ Possible access to various projects within our agency
â€¢ The opportunity to work with exclusive products
â€¢ $60 for participating in the filming day

Why this opportunity is valuable:
â€¢ This is a real chance to enter the TikTok Live Commerce industry.
â€¢ Participants go through a selection process - we choose motivated, attentive, and standout individuals.
â€¢ Filming takes place in a studio format. Please come in a neat yet bright look. Charismatic outfits are very welcome.

ðŸ“ž To apply, please send:
 1. Your photos

via Telegram / WhatsApp / Messenger: 747-286-83-92 Karina

Experience is not required - what matters is respect for the process, interest in the industry, and the desire to grow.

Whether youâ€™re preparing for auditions, looking to build technique, or just getting started, we welcome you to join us!

Sharing on behalf of BetweenGigs Casting!!

New Hampshire Casting Call for Union & Non-Union Actors!!

Casting is NOT restricted to New England!! 

Casting for a Sci-Fi trailer.

Casting two actors for a proof-of-concept trailer for an episodic sci-fi thriller. It will be shot at the state of the art Studio Lab facility in Derry NH in mid January. This is a paid gig. Both union and non union talent may submit. A Travel/Lodging budget is available, should talent cast be from outside the New England market.

Please see the details below and submit your materials to casting@humanoriginals.com by end of day Sunday, November 23. Please include contact information for your agent or manager if you have one.

************
Project Title: Resonance: Earth 101
Project Type: Proof-of-Concept Trailer
Union: SAG-AFTRA (Micro-Budget Agreement Pending): Roles are open to both union & non union actors.
Production Company: HumanOriginals
Usage: Online, and client/investor/distributer presentations

Shoot Dates: Two days. Tentatively scheduled for January 13 & 14 2026

Shoot Location: Studio Lab, Derry NH

Fit Date/Table Read: TBD. A stipend will be available
Tech Rehearsal Dates (1-2): TBD. A stipend will be available
Travel Stipend/Lodging: TBD, depending on talent's travel distance.

Shoot/Usage Compensation: $1,000/day per talent.
Meals, credit, and copy will also be provided.

SYNOPSIS
Resonance: Earth 101 is a sci-fi thriller proof-of-concept trailer.

Shortly after crashing on Earth in 1983, Kara discovers a mysterious VHS tape in an abandoned warehouse. This triggers a recorded message from Josh, a Brooklyn teen who seems to know her story, even before theyâ€™ve met. Through his nervous humor, warnings about Earth, and a mixtape he calls â€œEarth 101", Josh offers Kara both survival tools and an unexpected connection.

ROLES
JOSH
â€¢ Male, 18â€“25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
â€¢ A hidden tech prodigy from 1983 Brooklyn â€” sharp, curious, and socially awkward, hiding brilliance behind sarcasm. Nervous yet magnetic. He risks everything to help Kara find her way on Earth.

KARA
â€¢ Female, 18â€“25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
â€¢ A resilient and observant young woman carrying a maturity beyond her years. Athletic and graceful, Kara looks both innocent and ancient, as though sheâ€™s already written into myth. Her arrival on Earth sets off an unexpected chain of events.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS
To be considered for an audition, please email headshot (or current photo), resume, and reel (if available) to casting@humanoriginals.com.

Subject Line of your email should read: Role name / Your name

Submissions are requested by 5:00pm Sunday, November 23. 

If selected to audition, instructions & script for a self-taped audition will be sent to you.

Callbacks, if needed, will be via Zoom.

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew!

Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply for grants that align with the series' message, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.
